---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";

const mentorEntries = await getCollection("mentors");
const PANEL = mentorEntries
  .map((m) => ({
    id: m.id,
    name: m.data.name,
    avatar_initials: m.data.avatar_initials,
    accent: m.data.accent,
    short_bio: m.data.short_bio,
    style_notes: m.data.tells.slice(0, 2).join(" · ") || m.data.short_bio,
    sort_order: m.data.sort_order,
  }))
  .sort((a, b) => a.sort_order - b.sort_order);
---

<Layout title="Methodology · 100 Apps Journey">
  <article>
    <header class="border-b border-rule">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 pt-12 sm:pt-20 pb-10">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5 entry-rise">
          <span class="block w-6 h-px bg-seal"></span>
          <p
            class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-seal"
          >
            Methodology
          </p>
        </div>
        <h1
          class="font-display text-[2.5rem] sm:text-[3.5rem] font-medium tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[0.95] entry-rise"
          style="animation-delay: 0.05s"
        >
          Why 100 apps<br />in 100 days.
        </h1>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section>
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 py-12 sm:py-16">
        <div class="prose-journal">
          <p>
            AI has compressed the cost of building a working prototype from
            weeks to hours. The constraint is no longer engineering — it is
            <em>knowing what to build</em>. The most efficient way to find out
            is to build, ship, observe, and decide.
          </p>

          <p>
            This site is the public ledger of one such experiment: 100 small
            app attempts in 100 days. Each attempt is treated like an angel
            investment — a thesis, a kill criterion, a time budget. Most will
            fail. A few will hint at something. The portfolio approach assumes
            you don't know in advance which one is the outlier; you find out
            by trying.
          </p>

          <h2>The Frame</h2>
          <p>Every entry has four required fields, treated as the contract:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Thesis</strong> — why this could be valuable, in one or
              two sentences.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Kill criteria</strong> — the conditions under which this
              gets retired without sentiment.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Time budget</strong> — the cap on investment before
              re-evaluation.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Tags</strong> — domain markers for later
              pattern-finding.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-12 border-rule" />

        <div class="prose-journal">
          <h2>The Panel</h2>
          <p>
            Every idea is evaluated by an AI-simulated panel of five real
            investors and builders. Each is prompted to reason as themselves —
            drawing from their public writings, talks, and tweets — without
            artificial division of labor. They overlap, disagree, and bring
            their full perspective.
          </p>
        </div>

        <ul class="mt-6 grid gap-3">
          {
            PANEL.map((p) => (
              <li class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-4 items-start py-3 border-t border-rule first:border-t-0">
                <span
                  class="flex items-center justify-center w-9 h-9 rounded-full font-mono text-[11px] font-medium shrink-0"
                  style={`background-color: color-mix(in oklch, ${p.accent} 12%, transparent); color: ${p.accent};`}
                >
                  {p.avatar_initials}
                </span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-display font-semibold text-ink leading-tight">
                    {p.name}
                  </p>
                  <p class="font-body italic text-sm text-ink-soft mt-1 leading-snug">
                    {p.short_bio}
                  </p>
                  <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-ink-soft mt-1.5">
                    {p.style_notes}
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-6 font-body italic text-xs text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Evaluations are AI-generated simulations, not actual statements or
          endorsements of these individuals.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-12 border-rule" />

        <div class="prose-journal">
          <h2>The Promise</h2>
          <p>
            Most experiments are throwaway. That is the point. The compounding
            asset is not any single app — it is the <em>discipline</em> of
            writing thesis, kill criteria, and time budget for everything; of
            not falling in love with ideas; of letting the panel disagree
            productively. By day 100, the portfolio speaks for itself.
          </p>
          <p>
            And by day 200, two or three of the experiments will have outgrown
            the ledger and become real products. That is the bet.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="mt-16 pt-6 border-t border-rule font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-soft"
        >
          <a href="/" class="hover:text-seal transition-colors">
            ← Back to the Pipeline
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
